-- South Korea’s Household Bank Loans Rise to 459.3 Trillion Won
-- B y   C y n t h i a   K i m
-- 2012-09-12T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-12/south-korea-s-household-bank-loans-rise-to-459-3-trillion-won.html
South Korea’s bank lending to
households rose by 1.5 trillion won ($1.3 billion) last month to
459.3 trillion won, the  Bank of Korea  said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Mortgage lending rose 0.7 trillion won to 311.6 trillion
won, today’s report showed. Loans to companies gained 3.7
trillion won to 590.2 trillion won.  The broadest measure of  money supply , M2, rose 0.9 percent
in July from the previous month after a 0.4 percent gain in
June, according to a separate central bank statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cynthia Kim in Seoul at 
